data.description: YOUR FLORIDA OASIS AWAITS! Your new 3-bedroom, 2-bathroom, 2-car garage home in the Rotonda West White Marsh neighborhood was built in 2015 and has 1,600 sq. ft. of living space. LOW MAINTENANCE LANDSCAPE and room for a pool. The first thing you will notice as you drive up are the clean lines of the home and the easy-to-care-for tropical landscaping. OPEN-CONCEPT SPLIT FLOORPLAN WITH CATHEDRAL CEILINGS. As you step through the front door onto the inviting ceramic tile flooring you will notice how open, light, and bright it is. You have a living room that is open to a formal dining room, kitchen, and breakfast nook with bay windows right next to the open kitchen. KITCHEN WITH RAISED BREAKFAST BAR. Your new cozy kitchen comes complete with Corian countertops (and they look like marble), dishwasher, stainless-steel refrigerator, stove and a built-in microwave. You also have plenty of canned lighting and a decorator ledge above the cabinets making it perfect for adding your personal touches. And, you also have a built-in bar area that is perfect for those quick grab-and-eat meals. It’s also great for entertaining, as a buffet area, or just the fact that it enables you to cook, clean, and watch TV all at the same time. MASTER BEDROOM WITH ENSUITE AND GARDEN TUB. The master bedroom has plenty of room for all your things and comes with a huge walk-in closet. The ensuite is amazing. It has a wall-to-wall mirror, a separate double vanity area, and a huge garden tub perfect for relaxing after a long day. SECONDARY BEDROOMS. The secondary bedrooms are on the other side of your house and there is a bathroom in the hallway between them. LAUNDRY ROOM WITH STORAGE NOOK. Your new home also has a large laundry room with a storage nook full of shelves. You can never have too much storage! NICE SCREENED LANAI. You now have a place where you can sit and relax sipping your favorite beverage as you watch the sunrise and sunset while enjoying the tropical vibe of your back and side yards. A 5’x12’ and 9’x12’ concrete pads next to Lanai; Fruit trees include Prince Peach, Persian Lime, Bailey’s Marvel Mango, Lemon, Papaya, and Loquat Tree. ADDITIONAL FEATURES: Hurricane shutters, flagpole, professionally hung blinds in Master Bedroom and Living Room. New Roof and 6” gutters and downspouts installed August 2023, A/C serviced every 6 months. Flood Insurance NOT required.  ENVIABLE FLORIDA LOCATION. Your new home has a location that can’t be beat! You are close to all the white sandy beaches along the Gulf Coast. You also have the Myakka River, Lemon Bay, Lemon Bay Aquatic Preserve, and Gasparilla Sound-Charlotte Harbor. You are also close to the Rotonda Community Park and Preserve, Cape Haze Aquatic Preserve, Boca Grande, Gasparilla Island State Park, Cayo Costa State Park, and all the other attractions Florida has to offer. If you want convenience, you are close to many shops, restaurants, and grocery stores, and the hospital is not too far away. The handmade curtains do not convey. Furniture is avaible for purchase outside of home purchase.CALL TODAY TO SCHEDULE A SHOWING!
